      • getArgumentsMismatchMessage

        default MessageKey getArgumentsMismatchMessage()
        Returns the message to show to the user if the command is used with the wrong arguments. If null is returned, the standard help (/command help) output is shown.
        Returns:
        the message explaining the command's usage, or null for default behavior
